title: Thimisua
text:
Thimisua also known as Sidi-Bou-Argoub is an archaeological site in <a href="Tunisia">Tunisia</a>, located at 36.310720°N 9.319186° and which is known for the <a href="List%20of%20Roman%20amphitheatres">ampitheter</a> there. This structure is described as <a href="oval">oval</a> in <a href="shape">shape</a> with two entries and a longitudal axis.
During the <a href="Roman%20Empire">Roman Empire</a> the town of <a href="Thmisua">Thmisua</a> was a <a href="civitas">civitas</a> of <a href="Roman%20North%20Africa">Africa Proconsularis</a>. It was down stream from the <a href="Municipium">Municipium</a> of <a href="Thabbora">Thabbora</a> and it prospered from 330<a href="BCE">BC</a> to 640<a href="anno%20domini">AD</a>.
